@node "Changelog" "Changelog"
@{b}Complete changelog for the AmigaOS 4.x diskimage.device
Copyright (C) 2007-2014 Fredrik Wikstrom@{ub}

53.2 (30-Mar-2014)
- Updated CUE plugin to use the latest versioned shared object files.
- Updated GUI code to use OpenClass()/CloseClass() for opening and closing
  BOOPSI classes.
- Updated DMG and ISZ plugins to use Thore's now renamed bzip2.library.
- Updated AutoInstall script to use CopyStore for executable files.

53.1 (23-Mar-2014)
- MDS track mode detection now only looks at the 3 least significant bits.
- Added MODE 2 FORM 1 / 2448 support to MDS plugin.
- Added compiled in black and white fallback images same as in the m68k
  version (requires speedbar.gadget >= 53.11 because older AOS 4.x versions
  crash on non-BOOPSI button images).
- Updated to use Thore Boeckelmann's bz2.library.
- Updated to use application.library version 2 interfaces.

52.78 (23-Jul-2012)
- Fixed a bug in READ TOC command when TIME bit is set (the returned address
  should be 0MSF and not HMSF).

52.77 (24-Feb-2012)
- Updated Italian catalogs.
- Fixed ISO mounting which was broken by changes in previous version.

52.76 (21-Feb-2012)
- Rewrote HD_SCSICMD handling and moved some pretty general code away from
  plugins to the device where it belongs.
- Fixed code for saving and restoring the window sizes in DiskImageGUI.
- Improved the MDS plugin (should now be able to handle more MDS files than
  previously).
- WavPack plugin now uses WavpackGetBinaryTagItem() function as well as
  WavpackGetTagItem() to look for a WavPack embedded cuesheet.
- Updated German DiskImageGUI catalog.

52.75 (6-Sep-2011)
- Fixed a bug in the index parsing of CUE plugin (it would incorrectly return
  an error if the minute part was >= 60).
- Removed usage of deprecated XXXX_GetClass() functions.
- CUE plugin now only byteswaps audio tracks when MOTOROLA file type is used
  instead both data and audio tracks (not sure if this is correct or not).
- Added MODE 2 support in CCD plugin.

52.74 (13-Jun-2011)
- Updated Italian catalogs.
- Added support for WavPack files with embedded cuesheet information.
- Fixed WAVPACK_set_pos_rel callback implementation.

52.73 (5-Jun-2011)
- Fixed some pretty serious bugs in ReadTOC command introduced by the last
  released version.
- Updated plugin API to v7 (older plugins will no longer work).

52.72 (4-Jun-2011)
- Added support for non-zero track number in ReadTOC SCSI command.
- Added support for ReadCD SCSI command (needed by ADRipper program).

52.71 (18-May-2011)
- Completely rewrote and optimised all code for opening and closing libraries
  in plugins.
- Updated plugin API to v6 (older plugins will no longer work).
- Implemented VMDK plugin for handling .vmdk files.
- Implemented G64 plugin for handling .g64 files.

52.70 (1-May-2011)
- Fixed bug in MP3 support when seeking from EOF.
- Removed header size check in VDI plugin.
- Updated Italian catalogs.
- Implemented ISZ plugin for handling .isz files.

52.69 (23-Apr-2011)
- Now correctly ignores MPG123_NEW_FORMAT return from mpg123_read().

52.68 (23-Apr-2011)
- Replaced usage of mpega.library in CUE plugin with mpg123.library
  (mpg123.library has better seeking).
- Implemented OGG Vorbis support in CUE plugin using libvorbisfile.so.

52.67 (15-Nov-2010)
- Added a Turkish translation by Serkan Dursun.
- Updated Polish catalogs.
- Added support for FLAC files with embedded cuesheet information.

52.66 (16-Oct-2010)
- Updated German catalogs.
- Added AddReloadPluginsHook function to m68k jumptable.
- Changed DiskImageGUI PATTERN tooltype to "~(#?.info)" as it was getting too
  long for ASL to handle.
- Implemented FLAC support in CUE plugin using libFLAC.so.
- Implemented WavPack support in CUE plugin using libwavpack.so.
- External libraries opened by plugins are now closed when not needed any more.
- Added EJECT switch to MountDiskImage command.
- MountDiskImage now returns an error if neither DRIVE nor UNIT is specified.
- MountDiskImage now uses requesters if run from Workbench instead of writing
  to stdout/stderr.

52.65 (28-Aug-2010)
- Updated Italian catalogs.
- Scrollers are now updated correctly when scrolling using mouse wheel.

52.64 (26-Aug-2010)
- Updated German DiskImageGUI catalog.
- The image loader should no longer fail if there is a directory with the
  same name as the image somewhere in the image search path.
- Fixed a bug in the event handling code of the drive settings window.

52.63 (17-May-2010)
- Updated French and Italian catalogs.
- Drives with dg_DeviceType set to DG_CDROM or DG_OPTICAL_DISK are now shown
  with a small CD icon in DiskImageGUI.
- DiskImageGUI now allows configuring a device unit as either Direct Access,
  CD-ROM or Optical Disk.

52.62 (11-May-2010)
- DiskImageGUI has been rewritten from scratch so that it now has screen
  notify support and hopefully less bugs as well.
- Added RELOADPLUGINS notification code to diskimage.device and DiskImageGUI.
- The DiskImageGUI listbrowser scrollers are now placed inside the window
  borders.
- diskimage.device now stores the name of the plugin if DITAG_Plugin was used
  when mounting the disk.

52.61 (6-May-2010)
- Updated German catalogs.
- Fixed MountDiskImage so that it doesn't need a ':' character at the end of
  the drive name any more.
- Implemented VDI plugin for VirtualBox disk images.
- Added an additional check for CCD and CUE formats to make sure that they
  contain text and not binary data.
- The DMG plugin now ignores any unsupported partition types (this makes some
  .dmg files work that didn't before).

52.60 (5-May-2010)
- Updated Italian catalogs.
- Fixed the empty error requesters when using the write protect function in
  DiskImageGUI.

52.59 (4-May-2010)
- Updated German and Polish catalogs.
- TD_GEOMETRY now returns IOERR_SUCCESS instead of TDERR_DiskChanged if no
  disk is in the drive.
- Removed the KEEPOPEN switch from the MountDiskImage command as it's not
  needed any more.
- Fixed lockup/crash when starting a second instance of DiskImageGUI.

52.58 (15-Apr-2010)
- Implemented the TD_REMOVE command (needed by some old filesystems).
- Added a 68k jumptable to diskimage.device for compatibility with the OS3.x
  ported version of this device.
- Increased the process priority to 4.

52.57 (30-Mar-2010)
- Fixed a longstanding bug in the TD_ADDCHANGEINT/TD_REMCHANGEINT support
  (it seems that IExec->Cause trashes the is_Node.ln_Pred and is_Node.ln_Succ
  fields in the interrupt). The new implementation not only works around this
  but should also be much safer.

52.56 (28-Mar-2010)
- The device now remembers which images were mounted the last time it was used
  and automatically mounts them at startup.
- Cleaned up and fixed the track offset and length calculations in the CUE
  plugin.
- Minor optimisations to the seeking in the CUE plugin MP3 support (still
  doesn't handle "random" CDDA accesses too well though).

52.55 (22-Mar-2010)
- Fixed the MP3 support in the CUE plugin.
- Implemented RIFF-WAVE and IFF-AIFF audio track support in the CUE plugin.

52.54 (21-Mar-2010)
- Updated Italian catalogs.
- Fixed a memory leak in the NRG plugin (track structures weren't freed on
  disk image unmount).
- Implemented MDS and CCD plugins for mounting .mds and .ccd files.
- Added support for MP3 audio tracks in the CUE plugin using mpega.library
  (this feature still needs some work as the audio is far from perfect ATM).

52.53 (17-Mar-2010)
- Implemented CUE plugin for mounting .cue files (has the same experimental
  CDDA support as the NRG plugin).

52.52 (16-Mar-2010)
- Updated Italian catalogs.
- Finally implemented a proper AutoInstall script for AmiUpdate (can also be
  to manually update a diskimage.device installation by typing the command
  "execute AutoInstall" into a CLI window).
- Implemented experimental CDDA support in the NRG plugin (only supports
  "READ TOC" and "READ MSF" commands currently which is just enough to use
  the OS4 CDFileSystem's CDDA tracks as AIFF files feature and to play the
  tracks with PlayCDDA).
- Fixed a bug in the handling of uncompressed data (PT_COPY) in the DMG
  plugin.

52.51 (9-Mar-2010)
- Removed all format specific code from the builtin Generic plugin (support
  for these formats will gradually be added back in in the form of other
  plugins).
- Added builtin D64 plugin for handling .d64 disk images (256 bytes per
  block).
- Added builtin ISO plugin for handling 2352 bytes per block .iso files.
- Added info on which plugins support writing to the DiskImageGUI "Plugins"
  window.

52.50 (8-Mar-2010)
- Fixed the CheckImage functions in several plugins (incorrectly used ">"
  comparison instead of ">=").
- Added ability to detect diskimage format by file footer as well as header
  (this function is now used by DMG and UIF plugins instead of relying on the
  filename extension).
- The Nero disk image format (NRG) is now properly supported through an own
  plugin instead of just being semi-supported by the Generic plugin (only the
  first track/session is supported for now though).

52.49 (4-Mar-2010)
- Rewrote and improved most of the DMG plugin code.
- Added BZLIB support to the DMG plugin using Joerg Strohmayer's bz2.library.
- Added ADC support to the DMG plugin (untested).
- The DMG plugin now only opens z.library/bz2.library when they are needed to
  decode a mounted disk image.

52.48 (2-Mar-2010)
- Updated French and Italian catalogs.
- Added a Swedish translation by Magnus Hammarstrom.
- Rewrote the plugin error reporting so that it doesn't need a mutex anymore.
- The DMG plugin now returns ERROR_NOT_IMPLEMENTED if it encounters an
  unsupported block type.
- Modified the DMS plugin so that it's now re-entrant and doesn't need any
  additional mutex protection.
- Now uses shared semaphore locks to protect read access to some global lists
  (units, plugins, ...) instead of mutexes.

52.47 (15-Feb-2010)
- Added Greek catalogs by Antonis Iliakis.
- Updated Italian catalogs.
- Fixed an error reporting bug in DiskImageGUI ("Error: %s").
- Fixed a problem with unreleased mutexes when using XAD, XPK and DMS plugins.

52.46 (27-Sep-2009)
- Updated Finnish catalogs.
- Added an error requester for when an image couldn't be found.
- Images are searched for in the following places (in order):
   - PROGDIR:
   - PROGDIR:Images/
   - SYS:Prefs/Presets/Images/
   - TBImages: (if available)

52.45 (16-Sep-2009)
- Updated French catalogs.
- Modified to use the OS4.0 ExamineDir() function when scanning for plugins
  instead of the now deprecated ExAll() function.
- Removed the AISS requirement as per Open Amiga guidelines.

52.44 (17-Aug-2009)
- Updated Italian catalogs.
- Fixed crashes in DiskImage command.
- DiskImage command now shows current progress as a percentage.
- DiskImage command now uses a 1 MB i/o buffer instead of reading just one
  block at a time.

52.43 (27-Jul-2009)
- Fixed a bug in the plugin interface definition (the last entry that
  signifies the end of the list was missing from the vector list).

52.42 (4-Jul-2009)
- Rewrote much of the device <-> unit process communication code.
- Fixed the code for reporting errors when mounting disk images (it could
  break if more than one disk image was being mounted at the same time).
- Updated the plugin API to v2 (plugins compiled for diskimage.device 52.41
  are no longer supported by the device).

52.41 (18-Jun-2009)
- Replaced all SignalSemaphores with Mutexes.
- Implemented TD_CHANGENUM, TD_CHANGESTATE and TD_PROTSTATUS as immediate
  commands.

52.40 (28-Nov-2008)
- Fixed snapshotting code for the plugins window.
- Removed D64FileSystem from archive as it is available separately, and fs1541
  is better for this purpose anyway.
- Updated Spanish catalogs.
- Added application.library support.
- Some bugs fixed.
- Added code for detecting .nrg files in ISO format.
- Added support for .iso files with 2352 bytes per block.

52.39 (15-Jul-2008)
- Updated Polish catalogs.
- Updated Italian catalogs.
- Updated Finnish catalogs.
- Fixed "Unit" column label in DiskImageGUI.
- Implemented disk change detection in DiskImageGUI.
- Added "Snapshot" buttons to DiskImageGUI window titlebars.
- Removed "Snapshot" menu items since they aren't needed anymore.
- Modified snapshotting so that all size data is saved to a .xml file in
  ENV/ENVARC, instead of one .winsize file for each window (this also means
  that windows will need to be resnapshotted when updating).

52.38 (27-Mar-2008)
- Added Polish catalogs.
- Added "Plugins" window to DiskImageGUI.
- Added "Use plugin" chooser to DiskImageGUI.

52.37 (20-Mar-2008)
- Removed debug output from FDI plugin.
- DiskImage command now outputs most common device errors as text also.
- DiskImage command now allows retry and ignoring of errors.
- FDI plugin now optimised for speed, not size.

52.36 (19-Mar-2008)
- Updated Spanish catalogs.
- FDI plugin for .fdi files.

52.35 (10-Mar-2008)
- Updated French catalogs.
- Updated German catalogs.
- Updated Italian catalogs.
- Changed unit process names to "diskimage unit %ld".
- The password and progress bar windows now use this as window title instead
  of "diskimage.device".
- DiskImage command now inhibits the filesystem when writing an image to disk.

52.34 (28-Feb-2008)
- Added German catalogs.
- Implemented Refresh button in DiskImageGUI.
- Added PLUGIN/K option to force the device to use a specific plugin.
- Crypt plugin (should be compatible with crypt.device but this is not tested).

52.33 (25-Feb-2008)
- Removed debug output from DMG plugin.
- Plugins now only open libraries/devices when they are first needed.
- Reduced priority of XAD/XPK plugins.
- DAX plugin for .dax files.

(13-Feb-2008)
- DiskImage command was missing from archive.
- CPC plugin for CPCEmu disk images (non-EXTENDED only ATM).

52.32 (11-Feb-2008)
- Updated Italian catalogs.
- GI plugin for .gi files.
- DiskImage command for creating disk image files and writing them to disk
  (works on disk drives, harddrive partitions, etc., has NSD64 support).
  Note: if you use it to create an image of your SYS: partition your computer
  may appear to lock up while the read is in progress.

52.31 (10-Feb-2008)
- Reduced the memory requirements for the DMG plugin.
- Fixed a bug in the DMG/UIF buffering code.
- DAA plugin for .daa files.

52.30 (9-Feb-2008)
- All plugins now have version strings.
- Fixed missing return statement in the DMG plugin.
- UIF plugin for .uif files.
- Added some simple buffering code to the DMG plugin same as in the UIF plugin
