52.8 (9-Jun-2007)
- Added IPC0 mount file for fat (ms-dos) disk images.
- Added IEXT mount file for ext2 (linux) disk images (uses EXT2FileSystem
  which can be downloaded from Aminet).
- Added file pattern support to DiskImageGUI via PATTERN tooltype.
- Added .nrg support.

52.7 (3-Jun-2007)
- Now opens a requester when a needed support library is missing (f.e. when
  trying to mount an .ipf with no capsimage.device or an .adz with no
  z.library).
- Added .dms support (should also work with encrypted ones too but this code
  is untested so please report to me if there are problems with it).

52.6 (2-Jun-2007)
- "About" requester in DiskImageGUI.
- Opening the DiskImageGUI window / changing the write protection of a disk
  no longer causes the device units' diskchange interrupts to be run.
- Fixed TD_EJECT for IPF files.
- Added .adz support through the OS4 native z.library by Johan Gill.

52.5 (31-May-2007)
- Fixed a couple of memory trashing bugs in the device code that could cause
  crashes/lockups when mounting disk images.
- Added .ipf support through capsimage.device.

52.4 (30-May-2007)
- DiskImageGUI icon was missing from previous archives (fixed).
- Added WP=WRITEPROTECT/S option to MountDiskImage command.
- Added some error requesters to DiskImageGUI.

52.3 (29-May-2007)
- Added support for write protection (device and GUI).
- Added NSD64 and TD64 command support.
- Device should have no problems with disk images >4GB as long as the
  underlying filesystem also supports this (current available filesystems do
  not) - thanks to joerg for testing this.
- Fixed a small bug in the GUI (clicking "Insert" with no unit selected).

52.2 (28-May-2007)
- Added DiskImageGUI program.

52.1 (27-May-2007)
- First released version.

@endnode
@node "MountDiskImage" "MountDiskImage"
@{b}MountDiskImage@{ub} UNIT/K/N,DEVICE=DRIVE/K,FILE,WP=WRITEPROTECT/S,
@{tab}PASSWORD/K,RELOADPLUGINS/S,PLUGIN/K

@{b}CLI Usage:@{ub}

 - @{b}UNIT/K/N@{ub}
   diskimage.device unit number
 - @{b}DEVICE=DRIVE/K@{ub}
   Device name (f.e. IDF0:, ICD0:, ...)
 - @{b}FILE@{ub}
   Name of disk image file to mount
 - @{b}EJECT@{ub}
   Eject the currently inserted disk
 - @{b}WP=WRITEPROTECT/S@{ub}
   Mount image as writeprotected
 - @{b}PASSWORD/K@{ub}
   Password for password encrypted files/archives
 - @{b}RELOADPLUGINS/S@{ub}
   Force device to reload all plugins (will unmount all device units)
 - @{b}PLUGIN/K@{ub}
   Force device to open file with a specific plugin (required in order to use
   the Crypt plugin f.e.)

@{b}Examples:@{ub}

 - Mount filename.iso on ICD0:
   @{i}@{b}MountDiskImage @{ub}DRIVE ICD0: filename.iso @{ui}

 - Mount filename.adf on IDF0: as writeprotected:
   @{i}@{b}MountDiskImage @{ub}DRIVE IDF0: filename.adf WP @{ui}

 - Mount a single-partition hardfile on IDF0:
   @{i}@{b}MountDiskImage @{ub}DRIVE IDF0: filename.hdf @{ui}

 - Mount an RDB hardfile on diskimage.device unit 100:
   @{i}@{b}MountDiskImage @{ub}UNIT=100 rdb.hdf @{ui}
   @{i}@{b}Mounter @{ub}D=diskimage.device U=100 @{ui}

 - Mount an encrypted image file
   @{i}@{b}MountDiskImage @{ub}PLUGIN=crypt image.bin @{ui}

@{b}WB Usage:@{ub}

When MountDiskImage is set as the @{i}"Default Tool" @{ui}of a disk image file and
@{i}"Start from:" @{ui}is set to Workbench. The file will be mounted using options
specified in the icon's tooltypes.

Currently the following options can be used:
 - @{b}UNIT/K/N@{ub}
 - @{b}DEVICE=DRIVE/K@{ub}
 - @{b}WP=WRITEPROTECT/S@{ub}
 - @{b}PASSWORD/K@{ub}
 - @{b}PLUGIN/K@{ub}

@endnode
@node "Installation" "Installation"
@{b}Installation:@{ub}

The following instructions are for manually installing the device and its
associated files. It is recommended that you use the included Install script
instead as it makes the installation process somewhat easier.

@{b}Installation (manual):@{ub}

Start by opening a CLI and CD:ing to the diskimage_device directory. Then type
the following commands into the CLI to install the device and associated files:
Copy Devs/#? ALL TO DEVS:
Copy C/#? TO C:
Copy DiskImageGUI#? TO SYS:System/
Copy Catalogs/~(#?.#?) ALL TO LOCALE:Catalogs/

@{b}Installation (update):@{ub}

Updating an existing diskimage.device installation is as easy as executing the
included AutoInstall script (just open a CLI and type "Execute AutoInstall").
@endnode
@node "FixHDF" "FixHDF"
@{b}FixHDF @{ub}FILE/A,BLOCKSPERTRACK/N,SURFACES/N,BLOCKSIZE/N,CYLINDERSIZE/N

@{b}CLI Usage:@{ub}

Used to correct the file size of invalid sized hardfiles (removes extra unused
bytes that may cause the file not to mount correctly with the device). Assuming
a "standard" geometry of:
BlocksPerTrack = 32
Surfaces = 1
BlockSize = 512
then only the filename of the hdf will need to be given to the command.

If @{b}CYLINDERSIZE/N @{ub}is specified all other options except for @{b}FILE/A @{ub}will be
ignored.
@endnode
@node "DiskImage" "DiskImage"
@{b}DiskImage DRIVE/A,DISKIMAGE/A,WRITE/S @{ub}

@{b}CLI Usage: @{ub}

 - @{b}DRIVE/A @{ub}
   DOS device name (f.e. DF0:, CD1:, HD2:, ...)
 - @{b}DISKIMAGE/A @{ub}
   Disk image filename
 - @{b}WRITE/S @{ub}
   Use if you want to write a disk image file back to disk

@{b}Examples: @{ub}

 - Create diskimage file from disk in DF0:
   @{i}@{b}DiskImage @{ub}DF0: diskimage.adf @{ui}

 - Write diskimage file to disk in DF0:
   @{i}@{b}DiskImage @{ub}DF0: diskimage.adf WRITE @{ui}

 - Create diskimage file from disk in CD0:
   @{i}@{b}DiskImage @{ub}CD0: diskimage.iso @{ui}

 - Create diskimage file from harddrive partition DH2:
   @{i}@{b}DiskImage @{ub}DH2: diskimage.hdf @{ui}
@endnode
@node "Requirements" "Requirements"
@{b}Requirements@{ub}

 - AmigaOS >= 4.1

 - capsimage.device (IPF plugin) - http://softpres.org

 - z.library >= 52.1 (CSO, DAA, DAX, DMG, ISZ, UIF and VMDK plugins) -
   http://aminet.net/util/libs/z_library.lha

 - bzip2.library >= 53.1 (DMG and ISZ plugins) - included with MUI 4.0

 - expat.library >= 4.1 (DMG plugin) -
   http://os4depot.net/share/development/library/misc/expat-ppc.lha

 - mpg123.library >= 52.1 (MP3 audio tracks) -
   http://os4depot.net/share/library/audio/mpg123_lib.lha

 - libFLAC.so (FLAC audio tracks) -
   http://os4depot.net/share/development/library/audio/libflac.lha

 - libwavpack.so (WavPack audio tracks) -
   http://os4depot.net/share/development/library/audio/libwavpack.lha

 - Vorbis and ogg shared objects (Ogg Vorbis audio tracks) -
   http://os4depot.net/share/development/library/audio/libvorbis.lha
   http://os4depot.net/share/development/library/audio/libogg.lha

 - CBM1541FileSystem (D64/G64 files) -
   http://os4depot.net/share/driver/filesystem/cbm1541_fs.lha

 - SAMDOSFileSystem (SAD/DSK files) -
   http://os4depot.net/share/driver/filesystem/samdos_fs.lha

 - XISOFileSystem (XISO files) -
   http://os4depot.net/share/driver/filesystem/xiso_fs.lha

@{b}Recommended:@{ub}

 - AISS (DiskImageGUI) - http://masonicons.info/
@endnode
@node "Disk Image Formats" "Disk Image Formats"
@{b}Supported Disk Image Formats: @{ub}

 - adf    (Amiga Disk File)
 - adz    (gzipped adf file)
 - bin
 - ccd    (CloneCD)
 - cso    (Compressed ISO)
 - cpr    (same format as dsk)
 - cue
 - d64    (C=64)
 - daa
 - dax
 - dmg    (Apple disk image format)
 - dms    (DiskMaSher)
 - dsk    (CPCEmu, non-EXTENDED images only)
 - flac   (with embedded cue file)
 - g64    (C=64)
 - gi     (untested)
 - hdf
 - img
 - ipf    (needs capsimage.device)
 - iso    (CD/DVD)
 - isz
 - mdf    (Daemon Tools/Alcohol)
 - mds    (Daemon Tools/Alcohol)
 - nrg    (Nero)
 - raw
 - sad    (Sam Coupe)
 - toast  (Roxio Toast)
 - uif    (MagicISO)
 - vdi    (VirtualBox)
 - vmdk   (VMWare)
 - wv     (with embedded cue file)
 - xiso   (X-Box ISO)

@{b}Also supports compressed images through (if available): @{ub}

 - xadmaster.library
 - xpkmaster.library

Some plugins (f.e. DMS, XAD and XPK) will unpack to a temporary file in T:
(or a path specfied by the DiskImageTempPath env variable). In order to save
changes made to this file simply make a copy of the file to your harddrive.

Not all plugins have write support implemented. In this case the disks will
behave as if they were write protected.
@endnode
